===========================================================================
                    GPL VERSION COMPATIBILITY
===========================================================================

All heritage code permits redistribution under later GPL versions:

  Source                    | Original License | Permits GPL v3?
  --------------------------+------------------+----------------
  IRC (Oikarinen, 1988)    | GPL v1+          | Yes
  ircu2 (Undernet, 1990)   | GPL v1+          | Yes
  ircu2 (1998+ files)      | GPL v2+          | Yes
  Nefarious2 (2004)        | GPL v2+          | Yes
  Nefarious2 (some files)  | GPL v3+          | Yes (native)
  Cathexis (2026)           | GPL v3+          | Yes (native)
  ircd_md5.c               | Public Domain    | Yes (no restrictions)
  ircd_reslib.c (UC Berk)  | BSD 4-Clause     | Yes (permissive)
  ircd_reslib.c (DEC)      | DEC Permissive   | Yes (permissive)
  ircd_reslib.c (ISC)      | ISC License      | Yes (permissive)
  install-sh               | MIT/X11          | Yes (permissive)
  tests/iauth-test         | GPL v2 only      | No* (standalone script)

* tests/iauth-test is GPL v2 only (no "or later" clause). It is a
  standalone test script not compiled into or linked with the daemon
  binary. The daemon itself is not affected.

The combined work (the ircd daemon) is distributed under GPL v3 or later.

No Apache or LGPL licensed code exists in this codebase.

===========================================================================
              HERITAGE FILES WITHOUT PER-FILE HEADERS
===========================================================================

The following heritage files from ircu2/Nefarious2 do not contain
per-file license headers. They are part of the GPL-licensed project
distribution and are covered by the project-level GPL:

Source files:
  ircd/crule.c         — Tony Vencill (Tonto), author attribution only
  ircd/ircd_res.c      — Hybrid Group rewrite of Darren Reed's res.c,
                          informal "buy us a beer" permissive notice
  ircd/memdebug.c      — No header (debug allocator wrapper)
  ircd/test/*.c        — Test harnesses, no headers (5 files)

Header files (31 files):
  include/IPcheck.h     include/crule.h       include/fileio.h
  include/ircd.h        include/ircd_cloaking.h
  include/ircd_crypt_native.h  include/ircd_geoip.h
  include/ircd_osdep.h  include/ircd_reslib.h
  include/ircd_signal.h include/ircd_string.h include/list.h
  include/match.h       include/memdebug.h    include/opercmds.h
  include/packet.h      include/parse.h       include/querycmds.h
  include/random.h      include/res.h         include/s_bsd.h
  include/s_conf.h      include/s_debug.h     include/s_misc.h
  include/s_numeric.h   include/s_serv.h      include/s_user.h
  include/send.h        include/version.h     include/whocmds.h

These files have been distributed as part of the ircu2 and Nefarious2
GPL-licensed source distributions since the 1990s. The absence of
per-file headers does not change their license status — they are
governed by the project-level GPL as derivative components of the
original IRC daemon.
